<% content_for :title do %>
  Amped Up Aviation
<% end %>
<div style="height: 100px;"></div>
<div class="mx-5 text-light">
  <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mx-0 mb-5">
    <div class="col-auto text-center">
      <%= image_tag("amped_up_logo.jpg", alt: "Amped Up Aviation", height: 80) %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-auto ps-4">
      <p class="fw-bold font-monospace my-0" style="font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem);">VR Developer</p>
      <p class="text-opacity-75 font-monospace my-0" style="font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);">May 2024 &ndash; December 2024</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="height: 40px;"></div>
  <div class="row mx-0 justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-9 col-xxl-8">
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        Amped Up Aviation was a government-funded incubator operating in partnership with Flightline Training
        Services, formed in response to the devastating impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on the Canadian aviation
        industry. Its mission was to raise awareness of aircraft maintenance engineering as a viable and rewarding
        blue-collar career path, specifically targeting high school students exploring their options outside of
        traditional post-secondary routes.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        As a VR Developer on the project, I prototyped and built interactive VR applications in Unity3D and C#,
        translating design concepts into production-ready experiences. The goal was to give young people an
        immersive, hands-on glimpse into the world of aviation maintenance — making a technically demanding trade
        feel accessible and exciting to a new generation.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        I optimized real-time graphics pipelines for Meta Quest headsets and WebGL, improving frame rates by 20%,
        and integrated photorealistic Blender-designed 3D models to enhance immersion while reducing manual asset
        cleanup time by 30%. I also built automated test suites using the Unity Test Framework to ensure
        stability across multiple device targets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div style="height: 150px;"></div>